channel.title: Tor Browser ended with non-zero (error) exit code!
channel.description:
I got this error on one of my workstations in qubes-whonix. Is this an indicator of compromise on that vm? Or is this just some bug? It's only happening in one vm.
> torbrowser > Launching './Browser/start-tor-browser --detach --allow-remote'... > ./Browser/execdesktop: line 14: ./Browser/start-tor-browser: No such file or directory > [ERROR] [torbrowser] Tor Browser ended with non-zero (error) exit code! > > Tor Browser was started with: > /home/user/.tb/tor-browser/start-tor-browser.desktop --allow-remote . > > Tor Browser exited with code: 127 > > To see this for yourself, you could try: Start Menu -> System -> Xfce Terminal > Then run:
